The Kilifi government needs Sh500 million to address the hunger crisis affecting more than 200,000 residents, Agriculture chief officer Baha Nguma said yesterday.He spoke when he visited farmers at Gandini irrigation project in Magarini.&ldquo;If the county allocates a half a billion to my department and gives me six months only, I will make sure the locals do not seek relief food from outside," Nguma said.He said the county can use the River Sabaki for massive irrigation projects that will address famine.